$ SQL Server function: serverproperty
@ serverproperty

gh|about-MSSQL|/t-sql/functions/serverproperty/select-all.sql||

{ InstanceDefaultLogPath

 `serverproperty('InstanceDefaultLogPath')` returns the path to the → development/databases/SQL-Server/architecture/instance → development/databases/SQL-Server/architecture/transaction/log[log file].

}
{ InstanceName

 `serverproperty('InstanceName')` returns the → development/databases/SQL-Server/architecture/instance name if it is queried on a *named instance*.
  On a *default instance*, it returns → development/databases/SQL-Server/sql/null[`NULL`].

}
{ ProcessID

 `serverproperty('ProcessID')` helps to identify which `sqlsrvr.exe` process is related to an → development/databases/SQL-Server/architecture/instance.

}
{ ServerName

 `serverproperty('ServerName')` returns the string that is needed to connect to an → development/databases/SQL-Server/architecture/instance.

  The same value can also be obtained with → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/variables/atat#mssql-atat-servername[`@@servername`].

}

